eNCA’s senior reporter Dasen Thathiah chatted to Police Minister Bheki Cele at the Durban beachfront. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Police Minister Bheki Cele says he’s got nothing against liquor and partying, as long as it’s done responsibly. He was responding to the social media backlash he received after the country’s curfew was scrapped. READ: COVID-19 | Curfew lifted The COVID-19 curfew was lifted on Thursday following a special cabinet meeting. The meeting approved several changes to the Adjusted Level 1 COVID-19 regulations. * eNCA’s senior reporter Dasen Thathiah spoke to Cele.